23
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:09.720
It was scary at first, but after so much time speaking in English

24
00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:11.240
And learning about American culture,

25
00:02:11.620 --> 00:02:13.950
I knew I'd be able to make great business connections

26
00:02:13.970 --> 00:02:17.880
And sell directly to the customers who love my products and services.

27
00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:20.270
After just a few short years,

28
00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:24.090
I hired a sales team and a few managers to run the business for me.

29
00:02:25.030 --> 00:02:27.380
Now I only work about 10 hours a week

30
00:02:27.650 --> 00:02:31.400
And I spend the rest of my time traveling the world like I always dreamed about.

31
00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:36.730
Traveling the world was your dream too, wasn't it?

32
00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:41.880
Anyway, I'm just calling to say thank you, man.

33
00:02:41.950 --> 00:02:44.310
If you hadn't given up on your dream,

34
00:02:44.720 --> 00:02:47.170
I never would have been able to take those classes with Tony,

35
00:02:47.590 --> 00:02:53.250
Qualify for the exchange program, find a job, start a business, or travel the world.

36
00:02:54.370 --> 00:03:00.120
It's all thanks to your lack of dedication that I could take advantage of your missed opportunity.

37
00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:05.840
Thank you so much for not practicing your English. Peace!